description:
Bug 3666: Code Completion Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)
jkca (5/15/2001 11:04:56 AM)
Under certain circumstances, code assist eats too much code.
Consider the enclosed class.
As a programmer, I must add a parameter to the baz call in bar to make the program correct.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the enclosed class.
2. Go to the 'bar' method.
3. Notice that the 'baz' call is missing a parameter.

Observed behavior:
- The code in 'bar' is: baz(x.foo());

Expected behavior:
- The code should be changed to: baz(x.foo().foo());

EB: I would rather it gave me: baz(x.foo()x.foo());

public class X {
  void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo());
  }

  int foo() {
    return 5;
  }

  void baz(int i, int j) {
  }
}

KUM (5/21/01 9:02:11 AM)
